<$fill $name="body">

!! Plugin files

|!File |!Role |
|`components/pills.tid` |Pills facade component |
|`components/vtabs.tid` |Vertical tabs facade component |
|`core/menu.tid` |Generic element renderer |
|`core/mixins/bytype/*.tid` |Delegate mixins (view, click, visibility, class) |
|`core/mixins/state-handling.tid` |State tiddler/field computation |
|`core/mixins/utils.tid` |Sync utilities |
|`core/styles/bytype/*.tid` |Type-specific CSS |
|`showcase.tid` |Live demo |

!! Restart rules

|!Change |!Restart needed? |
|Edit existing `.tid` |No — filesystem-watcher syncs |
|Add/delete/rename `.tid` |Yes — directory scan at boot |

!! Creating a new facade

# Create `.tid` in `components/` directory
# Set title under `$:/plugins/rimir/components/`
# Add `\parameters` declaration with defaults
# `\import` needed mixins from `core/mixins/`
# Define `rrc0.elems`, `rrc0.elem-type`
# Define `rrc1.*` handlers (state, click, view)
# Add CSS (class-prefixed, not `@scope`)
# Transclude `core/menu` or inline the render loop
# Restart server

!! Adding an element type to vtabs

# Choose a type code (e.g., `sec`, `act`, `lnk`)
# Add click handler: `rrc1.elem-clicked:<type>`
# Add view slot in body-level `<%if%>` chain
# Add CSS for the type
# Add to `visible-types` default parameter

!! Known limitations

* `@scope` CSS is Chrome-only — use class-prefixed CSS instead
* `$slot` in procedures — see Architecture section
* No click slots in vtabs (hardcoded behaviors)

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="tip">
<$fill $name="body">CSS uses class prefixes (`.rrc-pills`, `.rrc-vtabs`) instead of `@scope` for Firefox compatibility.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
